## DEPLOYMENT: Step-by-Step

### 1. Backup current state
```bash
# Snapshot the droplet via DigitalOcean console
# Backup the database
pg_dump -h <host> -U doadmin -d defaultdb -F c -f backup_pre_deploy_$(date +%Y%m%d).dump
```

### 2. Manual DBA steps (connect as doadmin)
```sql
-- MUST be done before deploying new code
ALTER ROLE retailedge BYPASSRLS;

-- Verify
SELECT rolname, rolbypassrls FROM pg_roles
WHERE rolname IN ('retailedge', 'retailedge_app');
```

### 3. Deploy code
```bash
cd /path/to/retailedgeai
git pull origin main
cd server
npm install --production
npx prisma migrate deploy
npx prisma generate
```

### 4. Verify database state
```sql
-- Connect as doadmin
-- Check migrations applied
SELECT migration_name, finished_at FROM _prisma_migrations ORDER BY finished_at DESC LIMIT 5;

-- Check RLS policies (should show strict policies, no IS NULL fallback)
SELECT tablename, policyname, qual FROM pg_policies WHERE schemaname = 'public' LIMIT 20;

-- Check role permissions
SELECT rolname, rolbypassrls FROM pg_roles WHERE rolname IN ('retailedge', 'retailedge_app');
```

### 5. Restart application
```bash
pm2 restart all
pm2 logs --lines 50  # Watch for startup errors
```

### 6. Smoke tests
- [ ] Can access the landing page / marketing site
- [ ] Can register a new account (tests adminPrisma + auth flow)
- [ ] Can log in with the new account (tests JWT + tenant context)
- [ ] Can import a product (tests RLS enforcement on write)
- [ ] Can query the product back (tests RLS enforcement on read)
- [ ] Can connect Shopify (if applicable — tests integration routes)
- [ ] Can submit an AI query (tests ASAL + usage tracking)
- [ ] Admin routes work (tests adminPrisma BYPASSRLS)
- [ ] `/health` endpoint returns healthy status

